venues.name: Rogers Place

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Ticketmaster  Non-Sporting Events - 855-985-5000 Ticketmaster  Oilers - 780-414-GOAL (4625) Ticketmaster  Oil Kings - 780-414-GOAL (4625) Ticketmaster  Rogers Place - 780-414-LIVE (5483)
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Box Office is located on the southeast side of Rogers Place in the Ford Hall. Regular Hours: Monday to Friday: 9:00 AM to 4:30 PM Saturday, Sunday & Holidays: Closed Oilers/Oil Kings Games - Hours: Monday to Friday Games: 9:00 AM until beginning of third period. Saturday, Sunday & Holiday Games: 12:00 PM until beginning of third period. Concert/Live Entertainment Events - Hours: Monday to Friday Events: 9:00 AM until one hour after show start time. Saturday, Sunday & Holiday Events: 12:00 PM until one hour after show start time. Please note that box office hours are subject to change.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Debit, Visa, MasterCard, American Express, Cash
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: The Box Office is located on the southeast side of Rogers Place in Ford Hall. If picking up tickets, please arrive at box office early to avoid delays. Customers must present the actual credit card used to place the order and government issued photo ID. In an effort to offer every fan access to verified and secure tickets, online print and mobile access to ALL Rogers Place tickets will be available beginning 48 hours prior to event time.. Please note: You will still have access to view, transfer, or donate your seats prior to the 48 hour print access window.

venues.parkingDetail: There are more than 11,800 parking spots within a 10 minute walk of Rogers Place.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Place is fully accessible. Accessible seating is available in every seating level providing the same options available to all guests. In addition, all Executive Suites, Theatre Boxes and select Loge Tables are full accessible. Rogers Place can accommodate one attendant per barrier free guest. The attendant seats are located beside the barrier free position. If an attendant is not required then a single wheelchair seat can be purchased. Tickets are required for both the barrier free guest and attendant. Note: for concerts and various family shows/events, accessible seating may be reduced due to sightlines and restricted areas.

generalInfo.generalRule: No Smoking is allowed in Rogers Place. No outside food or beverages permitted. Cameras & Video equipment are not permitted. Ticket exchanges and refunds are not permitted. ROGERS PLACE ALCOHOL POLICIES ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE ON AN EVENT BY EVENT BASIS
generalInfo.childRule: Children under 24-months of age do not require a ticket if they are able to sit on the ticket holders lap and do not obstruct the view or comfort of other guests. Children aged 24-month and older do require a ticket. ROGERS PLACE CHILD POLICIES ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE ON AN EVENT BY EVENT BASIS

ada.adaCustomCopy: Customers who require accessible seating or are visually impaired, or are otherwise unable to complete a ticket purchase online, please call Ticketmaster Charge By Phone.
ada.adaHours: Call the Venue between 9.00 am and 5.00 pm

events.pleaseNote: Please note: Restaurant level seating does not include reservations in the Saddleroom Restaurant. Reservations can be made no earlier than one month prior to the event. Please call 777-3694 to book your dining reservations.

venues.name: Scotiabank Saddledome

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Ticketmaster Charge-by-Phone: 403.777.0000 Calgary Flames Seasons Tickets: 403.777.4646 Calgary Flames Customer Service: 403.777.4636 Please note: Restaurant level seating does not include reservations in the Saddleroom Restaurant. Reservations can be made no earlier than one month prior to the event. For Saddleroom Restaurant dining reservations only, please call 403.777.3694. This is not the number to purchase tickets.
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Monday to Friday: 9:00 am to 5:00 pm Saturday: 9:30 am to 4:00 pm Closed Sundays & Holidays On the day of an event the Box Office will open 2 hours prior to the event.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Interac, Visa, MasterCard, Sears, Diners Club and American Express.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Box Office Location: Main Box Office is located via 5th Street SE entrance Note: Please arrive at box office early if picking up tickets. Customers must present the actual credit card used to place the order and photo ID.

venues.parkingDetail: There is limited pay parking on the grounds. It is advisable to park at an LRT lot and take the train.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible Seating: Wheelchair areas are: Sections 103-105 - attendant can sit beside wheelchair Sections 218 and 220 - attendant must sit behind wheelchair. Wheelchairs cannot be placed in the FLOOR section due to fire regulations. The Wheelchair or Handicap entrance is located on the North East side of the Scotiabank Saddledome. Handicap parking is at the 5th street entrance. Hearing Devices: None.

generalInfo.childRule: For any events in which there are childrens or student discounts, children UNDER 24 months are admitted FREE of charge but they must sit on adults lap. For any event which does not have childrens discounts as mentioned above, all ages must pay including babes in arms.

accessibility.info:
Wheelchair and companion seating is available with a 1 to 1 arrangement in sections 103,117, 121, 302, 311, 317, 321 and 326.  A chair will be provided for the companion, who will be seated directly beside the wheelchair space.  Additional companion seats may be purchased in the adjoining sections, subject to availability. Depending on show configuration and production requirements, some sections may not be available for all events.

Where stage configuration allows, some non-hockey events also offer a section for Sight/Hearing impaired seating.

There are accessible spaces available in all parking lots and all venue washrooms are accessbile.

venues.name: Bell MTS Place (Formerly MTS Centre)

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Main Floor Box Office at Portage and Donald Monday to Friday: 10:00am to 5:00pm Saturday: 10:00am - 2:00pm Box Office is also open 2 hours prior to all events and remains open until 1 hour after event start time.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: VISA, MasterCard, American Express, Cash, Debit, TM Gift Cards
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Located at all Box Office windows. Customers must present the actual credit card used to place the order and photo ID. Only the owner of the credit card may pick up the tickets. Note that some orders cannot be picked up until the night of the show. Paperless tickets do not need to be picked up in advance, simply proceed to the gate if you have paperless tickets (see General Rules).

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is available at a wide variety of surface lots and parkades in the area, generally priced between $7 and $15 per car. See bellmtsplace.ca for additional information.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: There are a number of accessible platforms that can be purchased by patrons who require limited mobility access. Note that row 16 in the lower bowl has no stairs and may be a suitable option for some patrons. The best drop off point for wheelchairs is the loading zone on Donald between Portage and Graham.

generalInfo.generalRule: No professional cameras are allowed. No outside food or drink is allowed in the building. All patrons are subject to a search before entering. Paperless tickets require the purchaser to bring the actual credit card used and all members of the group in order to enter. There are access restrictions on concourse access based on your section and seat. Customers with lower bowl tickets are not allowed to access the upper bowl, and customers with upper bowl tickets do not have access to the lower concourse.
generalInfo.childRule: Each event has specific rules; some events may require all patrons to have a ticket and others may allow free admission for 24 months and under. Please contact Ticketmaster for details regarding any specific event.

ada.adaPhones: Ticketmaster: 1-855-682-6736 or any other Ticketmaster Charge by Phone Number
ada.adaCustomCopy: Customers who require accessible seating options including customers with visual disabilities, or who are otherwise unable to complete a ticket purchase online, please call Ticketmaster Charge by Phone.
ada.adaHours: Ticketmaster: Mondays to Saturdays 9:30am to 10pm EST; Sundays and statutory holidays from 12 noon to 8pm EST
